This new collaboration educational project devoted to the study and discussion of the book-to-screen adaptations was realised within the framework of cooperation between Poltava V.G. Korolenko National Pedagogical University and Université de Versailles Saint-Quentin-en-Yvelines (France) during 7 March – 11 April 2023.

The project was designed by Full Professor of Université de Versailles Saint-Quentin-en-Yvelines and Honorary Professor of Poltava V.G. Korolenko National Pedagogical University Jan Borm, Head of the Department of English and German Philology (PNPU) Dr Maryna Zuyenko, and Associate Professor of the Department of English and German Philology (PNPU) Dr Tetyana Lunyova. The Dean of the Faculty of Philology and Journalism Dr Oksana Kyrylchuk provided strong support for the implementation of the project.

The interactive seminars within the project were designed and conducted by the teachers of Université de Versailles Saint-Quentin-en-Yvelines Full Professor Jan Borm and Junior-Full Professor Joanna Kodzik and the teachers of Poltava V.G. Korolenko National Pedagogical University Dr Maryna Zuyenko (Head of the Department of English and German Philology), Dr Tetyana Lunyova (Associate Professor of the Department of English and German Philology), Dr Bogdan Storokha (Head of the Department of Romance and Germanic Philology). Dr Iryna Tyminska (Associate Professor of the Department of English and German Philology) contributed to creating the educational materials. Dr Valentyna Voskoboynyk and Dr Viktoriya Kravchenko (both Associate Professors of the Department of English and German Philology) helped PNPU students to prepare for the interactive seminars and took part in the seminars.

Each seminar within the project “Literature and Cinema” lasted 2 hours and was conducted in English via the platform Zoom. The following topics were covered within the project:

7 March 2023: French-Ukrainian teaching team conducted an introduction interactive seminar which included introductions of all the participants and overview of the topics selected for analysis and discussion;

14 March 2023: Dr Maryna Zuyenko and Dr Tetyana Lunyova – the film “A Matter of Life and Death” (1946);

21 March 2023 року: Junior-Full Professor Joanna Kodzik – the film “The Mission” (1986 р.);

28 March 2023: Dr Tetyana Lunyova – the film “Shadows of Forgotten Ancestors” (1964 р.);

4 April 2023: Professor Jan Borm – the film “On the Black Hill” (1987 р.);

11 April 2023: Dr Bogdan Storokha, Dr Maryna Zuyenko, and Dr Tetyana Lunyova – the film “Patience (After Sebald)” (2012).

The students from both universities highly appreciated the seminars in their feedbacks, they expressed the satisfaction with the relevance of the topics and the variety of interactive tasks.
